After leaving Paris Saint-Germain for free last June, Hatem Ben Arfa is preparing to sue his former club.
In its edition of the day, Le Parisien announces that the player should seize the Conseil de Prud’hommes. An approach which the club of the capital would have already been informed, through the agent of the player, Me Jean-Jacques Bertrand.
The player complains that he was “harassed weekly” when he was removed from the professional group for a period of time without having been retained in the PSG professional group for more than one year. Nearly 100,000 euros would be claimed by the player to his former club, he will find this Sunday in Ligue 1.
